            <bug_when>2009-12-14 16:24:56 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>With the change only to use the AlphaImageLoader for IE6 and IE8 in &quot;IE8 Standards Mode&quot; we should offer the &quot;-disabled&quot; images for all other IEs to optimize the PNG images whenever a widget is disabled.

Reason for this is that the applied opacity filter is looking bad for PNG images. To avoid this, we can offer a special &quot;-disabled&quot; image which replaces the original image in order to not use the opacity filter at all.</thetext>
